article.description: — Kaiden Rice had 21 points as The Citadel beat Wofford 77-69 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Rice scores 21 to lift The Citadel over Wofford 77-69
article.linkText: Rice scores 21 to lift The Citadel over Wofford 77-69
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- — Kaiden Rice had 21 points as The Citadel beat Wofford 77-69 on Wednesday night. Tyler Moffe had 18 points and six rebounds for The Citadel (9-4, 2-4 Southern Conference), which ended its four-game losing streak. Hayden Brown added 16 points, 14 rebounds and six assists. Storm Murphy had 16 points for the Terriers (9-5, 6-2), whose four-game winning streak was broken. Messiah Jones added 13 points and Max Klesmit had seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
